title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\prec \colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00NL.xml"
addr="jms-00NL"
title="Well-founded relation">well-founded relation</fr:link> and fix a subset <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subseteq  S]]></fr:tex> holds if and only if for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  y\in  A\mathpunct {.} y\prec  x\implies  y\in  S]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>In other words, to show that every element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> lies in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, it is enough to show that for any element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>, the elements below <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> lie in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
